<section id="fs-idm372439216" class="questions">
<exercise id="fs-idm370742992">
<problem id="fs-idm368423872">
<para id="fs-idm384863552"><link class="lo-reference" document="m68120"/>Explain margin of safety and why it is an important measurement for managers.</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm350176736">
<para id="fs-idm371703472">Answers will vary. Responses should include an explanation of how margin of safety allows the business to operate at a level where the risk of falling to or below the break-even point is low. There should also be some mention of the usefulness of the margin safety as an “alarm” for companies, such that when sales fall to the margin of safety level, action may be warranted.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
