<section id="fs-idm325815216" class="problem-set-a">
<exercise id="fs-idm380615664">
<problem id="fs-idm371759088">
<para id="fs-idm372528176"><link class="lo-reference" document="m68120"/>Jakarta Company is a service firm with current service revenue of $400,000 and a 40% contribution margin. Its fixed costs are $80,000. Maldives Company has current sales of $6,610,000 and a 45% contribution margin. Its fixed costs are $1,800,000.</para>
<list id="fs-idm370547888" list-type="enumerated" number-style="upper-alpha">
<item>What is the margin of safety for Jakarta and Maldives?</item>
<item>Compare the margin of safety in dollars between the two companies. Which is stronger?</item>
<item>Compare the margin of safety in percentage between the two companies. Now, which one is stronger?</item>
<item>Compute the degree of operating leverage for both companies. Which company will benefit most from a 15% increase in sales? Explain why. Illustrate your findings in an Income Statement that is increased by 15%.</item>
</list>
</problem>
</exercise>
